{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.37",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 37,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 37 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:1",
      "text": "Every friend saith, I am his friend also: but there is a friend, which is only a friend in name.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:2",
      "text": "Is it not a grief unto death, when a companion and friend is turned to an enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:3",
      "text": "O wicked imagination, whence camest thou in to cover the earth with deceit?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:4",
      "text": "There is a companion, which rejoiceth in the prosperity of a friend, but in the time of trouble will be against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:5",
      "text": "There is a companion, which helpeth his friend for the belly, and taketh up the buckler against the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:6",
      "text": "Forget not thy friend in thy mind, and be not unmindful of him in thy riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:7",
      "text": "Every counsellor extolleth counsel; but there is some that counselleth for himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:8",
      "text": "Beware of a counsellor, and know before what need he hath; for he will counsel for himself; lest he cast the lot upon thee,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:9",
      "text": "and say unto thee, Thy way is good: and afterward he stand on the other side, to see what shall befall thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:10",
      "text": "Consult not with one that suspecteth thee: and hide thy counsel from such as envy thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:11",
      "text": "Neither consult with a woman touching her of whom she is jealous; neither with a coward in matters of war; nor with a merchant concerning exchange; nor with a buyer of selling; nor with an envious man of thankfulness; nor with an unmerciful man touching kindness; nor with the slothful for any work; nor with an hireling for a year of finishing work; nor with an idle servant of much business: hearken not unto these in any matter of counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:12",
      "text": "But be continually with a godly man, whom thou knowest to keep the commandments of the Lord, whose mind is according to thy mind, and will sorrow with thee, if thou shalt miscarry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:13",
      "text": "And let the counsel of thine own heart stand: for there is no man more faithful unto thee than it;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:14",
      "text": "for a man's mind is sometime wont to tell him more than seven watchmen, that sit above in an high tower.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:15",
      "text": "And above all this pray to the most High, that he will direct thy way in truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:16",
      "text": "Let reason go before every enterprize, and counsel before every action.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:17",
      "text": "The countenance is a sign of changing of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:18",
      "text": "Four manners of things appear: good and evil, life and death: but the tongue ruleth over them continually.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:19",
      "text": "There is one that is wise and teacheth many, and yet is unprofitable to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:20",
      "text": "There is one that sheweth wisdom in words, and is hated: he shall be destitute of all food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:21",
      "text": "For grace is not given him from the Lord; because he is deprived of all wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:22",
      "text": "Another is wise to himself; and the fruits of understanding are commendable in his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:23",
      "text": "A wise man instructeth his people; and the fruits of his understanding fail not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:24",
      "text": "A wise man shall be filled with blessing; and all they that see him shall count him happy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:25",
      "text": "The days of the life of man may be numbered; but the days of Israel are innumerable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:26",
      "text": "A wise man shall inherit glory among his people, and his name shall be perpetual.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:27",
      "text": "My son, prove thy soul in thy life, and see what is evil for it, and give not that unto it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:28",
      "text": "For all things are not profitable for all men, neither hath every soul pleasure in every thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:29",
      "text": "Be not insatiable in any dainty thing, nor too greedy upon meats:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:30",
      "text": "for excess of meats bringeth sickness, and surfeiting will turn into choler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.37.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 37:31",
      "text": "By surfeiting have many perished; but he that taketh heed prolongeth his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
